      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>I recommend Thomas L. Friedman's ''Cover Story'' (column, Oct. 16) to those who view the peace process as the proverbial chicken-and-egg problem (Israeli intransigence versus Arab terrorism).</p>
        <p>If Mr. Friedman is correct, as I believe he is, that Israeli public opinion is a major lever on the actions of Israeli leaders and that opinion is shaped dramatically by fear of bombings, how difficult is it to conclude that Arab terrorism is the main obstacle to peace? The end of suicide bombings should yield concessions. Meanwhile, we are left with the conclusion that concessions yield suicide bombings.</p>
        <p>HOWARD  S. SCHIFFMAN</p>
        <p>Brooklyn, Oct. 16, 1997</p>
      </block>
